# Network Planning Guide

This guide outlines the essential steps for planning a reliable and secure LAN and WAN network.

---

## 📊 Project Scope
Define the purpose and scope of the network:
- Number of users and devices
- Network size (home, small office, multi-site)
- Required bandwidth and performance needs

---

## 🖧 IP Addressing and Subnetting
Plan the IP address schema for the network:
- Private IP range (e.g., 192.168.1.0/24)
- Subnetting for VLANs and departments
- Static IPs for critical devices (printers, servers)

---

## 🔑 Security Considerations
- Enable WPA3 for Wi-Fi
- Set up VLANs for traffic segmentation
- Configure firewall rules and access controls

---

## ⚙️ Hardware Requirements
List of required hardware:
- Router, Switch, Access Points
- Network cables (Cat5e, Cat6)
- Patch panels (for structured cabling)

---

## 📋 Documentation and Topology
- Create a network topology diagram
- Document IP addressing and VLAN assignments
- Prepare configuration backups

---

## 🚀 Deployment Steps
1. Configure router and switch
2. Set up VLANs and DHCP
3. Test connectivity and security controls

---

## 🛠️ Troubleshooting Tips
- Check cable connections
- Verify IP configuration
- Review firewall and VLAN settings

This guide ensures that your network is planned, organized, and secure before deployment.
